# Pressure Transfer Cellular Automaton

2D CA simulator for underwater acoustic pressure propagation (SMaRC PhD project).

## Directory Layout

```
src/                    # Core engine (importable module)
  pressure_transfer_ca.py
scripts/                # Runnable entry points
  run_experiment.py     # Config-driven runner → per-experiment dirs
  benchmark_backends.py
configs/                # YAML config files (one per experiment setup)
  default.yaml          # Fully documented template
experiments/            # Output: one timestamped subdirectory per run
  <name>/config.yaml    # Cloned config for reproducibility
  <name>/summary.png
  <name>/propagation.gif
```

## Config-driven experiments

All parameters live in YAML config files under `configs/`. The runner clones the config into the experiment output directory so results are self-contained.

```bash
python scripts/run_experiment.py --config configs/my_expt.yaml
python scripts/run_experiment.py --config configs/my_expt.yaml --steps 100 --no-gif  # CLI overrides
```

## Import pattern

Scripts in `scripts/` add `src/` to sys.path:
```python
sys.path.insert(0, str(Path(__file__).resolve().parent.parent / "src"))
from pressure_transfer_ca import PressureCASimConfig, run_pressure_transfer_ca
```

## Key physics

- Wave model: `c(y)^2 * Laplacian(p)` with CFL check, boundary reflections, absorption
- Transfer model: legacy CA with impedance interface, refraction, precomputed tables
- SSP interpolated onto grid, supports rectangular cells (dx != dy)
